'''倫敦運輸局'''（{{lang-en|Transport for London}}，縮寫為{{lang|en|'''TfL'''}}）是負責管理[[英國|英國]][[大倫敦|大倫敦地區]][[公共交通|大眾運輸]]{{link-en|運輸網|Transport network|系統}}的地方政府機關，其主要角色是將運輸政策或者計畫付諸執行，並且管理在倫敦的運輸服務<ref name="TfLFactsheet">{{cite web|url= http://www.tfl.gov.uk/assets/downloads/corporate/TfL_Factsheet_May_2008.pdf|title= Fact sheet: Transport for London|accessdate= 2008-09-06|format= [[Portable_Document_Format|PDF]]|publisher= Transport for London|date= 2008年5月|archive-date= 2018-12-26|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20181226033858/http://content.tfl.gov.uk/corporate/TfL_Factsheet_May_2008.pdf|dead-url= no}}</ref>。

== 管理 ==
倫敦運輸局是由其[[董事会|董事会]]管理掌控，董事会的成員則是由[[倫敦市長|倫敦市長]]指定，<ref name="TfLFactsheet" /> 該董事局主席一職目前由[[簡世德|簡世德]]擔任。[[倫敦運輸局專員|倫敦運輸局專員]]（彼得·亨第（Andy Byford）自2015年1月18日起擔任）負責向董事會報告，並領導一個管理團隊。

== 歷史 ==
倫敦運輸局根據[[1999年大倫敦權限法|1999年大倫敦權限法]]（Greater London Authority Act 1999），在2000年以[[大倫敦政府|大倫敦政府]]轄下單位的身分成立<ref name="TfLFramework">{{cite web |url=http://www.tfl.gov.uk/corporate/about-tfl/2881.aspx |title=Legislative framework |accessdate=2008-09-06 |publisher=Transport for London |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120123023657/http://www.tfl.gov.uk/corporate/about-tfl/2881.aspx |archivedate=2012-01-23 }}</ref>。在2000年成立之初，TfL接收了前任單位[[倫敦區域運輸局|倫敦區域運輸局]]（London Regional Transport）大部份的管轄範圍。但直到2003年，在與民營維護商簽訂爭議性的[[公私合作關係|公私合作關係]]（Public–private partnership，PPP）合約之後，倫敦運輸局才正式接管倫敦地鐵。而[[倫敦計程車|計程車]]的管理則曾經是[[倫敦警察廳|倫敦警察廳]]的職權範圍。

== 組織 ==
倫敦運輸局旗下有三個主要單位，每個單位負責管理不同的[[交通工具|運輸工具]]，這三個主要單位分別是：

* [[倫敦地鐵|倫敦地鐵]]，負責營運倫敦的地下鐵路系統，通常稱為「the tube」（管子之意），此外也負責管理與監督民間機構提供的維護服務。這個單位旗下又分為三個服務子單位：
** BCV：[[倫敦地鐵貝克盧線|貝克盧線]]、[[倫敦地鐵中央線|中央線]]、[[倫敦地鐵維多利亞線|維多利亞線]]以及[[倫敦地鐵滑鐵盧及城市線|滑鐵盧及城市線]]。 
** JNP：[[倫敦地鐵朱比利線|朱比利線]]、[[倫敦地鐵北線|北線]]以及[[倫敦地鐵皮卡迪利線|皮卡迪利線]]。
** SSR（淺層路線鐵路，Sub Surface Railway）：[[倫敦地鐵大都會線|大都會線]]、[[倫敦地鐵區域線|區域線]]、[[倫敦地鐵環線|環線]]和[[倫敦地鐵漢默史密斯及城市線|漢默史密斯及城市線]]。
* [[倫敦鐵路|倫敦鐵路]]（London Rail），負責以下業務：
** 與提供倫敦地區[[國家鐵路網|國家鐵路網]]服務的營運商協調合作。
** [[倫敦地上鐵|倫敦地上鐵]]：服務倫敦市區外圍的[[通勤鐵路|通勤鐵路]]系統。
** [[碼頭區輕便鐵路|碼頭區輕便鐵路]]：通常簡稱「''DLR''」，是位於[[東倫敦|東倫敦]]區域的自動駕駛[[輕軌運輸|輕軌運輸]]系統。但實際上的營運和維護是由民營機構負責。
** [[倫敦電車系統|倫敦電車系統]]，負責管理由民營企業簽約營運的倫敦[[有軌電車|有軌電車]]路線。目前僅有位於倫敦南部的[[電車連線|電車連線]]，但有其他路線正在規劃中。
* 路面運輸，包括：
** [[倫敦巴士|倫敦巴士]]，負責管理倫敦內的紅色巴士路線，大部份是由民間的私人巴士公司營運。
** [[倫敦身障叫車服務|倫敦身障叫車服務]]，提供身障交通車輛服務。
** [[倫敦游船服務|倫敦游船服務]]，負責協調和發送執照給[[泰晤士河|泰晤士河]]上的旅客運輸服務商。
** [[倫敦街道|倫敦街道]]，負責管理倫敦的街道。
** [[倫敦交通壅塞收費|倫敦交通壅塞收費]]。
** [[倫敦計程車|倫敦計程車]]，負責管理著名的[[倫敦計程車|黑色計程車]]以及私人出租車。
** [[維多利亞巴士總站|維多利亞巴士總站]]，倫敦交通局擁有並經營倫敦最大的遠距巴士車站。
** 優秀自行車中心（Cycling Centre of Excellence），在倫敦推廣騎乘自行車。
** 提供更好的人行道
** 倫敦道路安全小組（London Road Safety Unit），透過廣告推廣用路安全，並測量道路的安全指數。<!--, which promotes safer roads through advertising and road safety measure.
**[[Community_Safety,_Enforcement_and_Policing|Community Safety, Enforcement and Policing]], responsible for tackling fare evasion on buses, delivering policing services that tackle crime and disorder on public transport in cooperation with the [[Metropolitan_Police_Service|Metropolitan Police Service]]'s [[Transport_Operational_Command_Unit|Transport Operational Command Unit]] (TOCU) and the [[British_Transport_Police|British Transport Police]].
**Traffic Enforcement, responsible for enforcing traffic and parking regulations on the [[red_route|red route]]s 
**Freight Unit, which is currently developing the "London Freight Plan"<ref name="TfLFreight">{{cite web|url= http://www.tfl.gov.uk/businessandpartners/freight/1280.aspx|title= Freight|accessdate= 2008-09-06|publisher= Transport for London}}</ref> and is involved with setting up and supporting a number of [[Freight_Quality_Partnerships|Freight Quality Partnerships]] covering key areas of London.

Each of the main units has its own corporate identity, formed by differently-coloured versions of the standard [[roundel|roundel]] and adding appropriate lettering across the horizontal bar. The roundel rendered in blue without any lettering represents TfL as a whole (see Transport for London logo). The same range of colours is also used extensively in publicity and on the TfL website.

==資費==
[[Image:Roundelfamily.jpg|thumb]]。]]
Most of the transport modes that come under the control of TfL have their own charging and ticketing regimes. Buses and trams share a common fare and ticketing regime, and the DLR and the Underground another.

Superimposed on these mode-specific regimes is the [[Travelcard|Travelcard]] system, which provides zonal tickets with validities from one day to one year, and off-peak variants. These are accepted on the DLR, buses, railways, trams, the Underground and provides a discount on many river services fares.

The [[Oyster_card|Oyster card]] is a [[contactless_smart_card|contactless smart card]] system introduced for the public in 2003, which can be used to pay individual fares (Pay as you go (PAYG), formerly "prepay") or to carry various Travelcards and other passes. It is used by holding the card close to the yellow card reader (though touching it flat is recommended). Card readers are found on ticket gates where otherwise a paper ticket could be fed through, allowing the gate to open and the passenger to walk through, and on stand-alone Oyster validators, which do not operate a barrier. Oyster PAYG can only be used on a [[Oyster_card_(pay_as_you_go)_on_National_Rail|limited selection of National Rail routes in London]]. Oyster PAYG has a set of daily maximum charges that are cheaper than buying a Travelcard for those not using the parts of [[National_Rail|National Rail]] where Oyster PAYG is not valid.

== 旅程計畫 ==
TfL has developed an electronic "Journey Planner",<ref name="TfLJourneyPlanner">{{cite web|url= http://journeyplanner.tfl.gov.uk/|title= Journey Planner|accessdate= 2008-09-06|publisher= Transport for London}}</ref> which enables users to plan journeys by multiple modes in and around London. Accessible online, it is also available at [[Internet_kiosk|kiosk]]s and some [[payphone|payphone]]s throughout London.

== 酒精禁令 ==
[[File:Alcohol_ban_tube_party_june'08.jpg|thumb]]
On 1 June 2008, the drinking of [[alcoholic_beverage|alcoholic beverage]]s was banned on Tube and [[London_Overground|London Overground]] [[train|train]]s, [[bus|bus]]es, [[tram|tram]]s, [[Docklands_Light_Railway|Docklands Light Railway]] and all stations across London.<ref name="TfLAlcoholBan">{{cite web|url= http://www.tfl.gov.uk/corporate/media/newscentre/archive/8423.aspx|title= Alcohol ban comes into force on the Tube, trams and buses from this Sunday, 1 June |accessdate= 2008-09-06|date= 2008-06-30|publisher= Transport for London}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/london/7387113.stm|title= Johnson bans drink on transport |accessdate= 2008-09-06|date= 2008-05-07|publisher= [[BBC_News|BBC News]]}}</ref> Carrying open containers of alcohol was also banned on public transport. The [[Mayor_of_London|Mayor of London]] and TfL announced the ban with the intention of providing a safer and more pleasant experience for passengers.

There were "Last Round on the Underground" parties on the night before the ban came into force. Until [[bylaw|bylaw]]s are altered to incorporate the ban the only enforcement action available is confiscation of the alcohol and/or ejection from the London Transport network.<ref name="TfLAlcoholBan" />

==Mentions in 2006 honours list==
After the [[7_July_2005_London_bombings|bombings on the underground and bus systems]] on 7 July 2005, many staff were recognised in the [[New_Year_Honours_2006|2006 New Year honours list]] for the heroic work they did. They helped survivors out, removed bodies, and got the transport system up and running, to get the millions of commuters back out of London at the end of the work day. Those mentioned include [[Peter_Hendy|Peter Hendy]], who was at the time Head of Surface Transport division, and [[Tim_O'Toole|Tim O'Toole]], head of the Underground division, who were both awarded [[Order_of_the_British_Empire|CBE]]s.

